*ipsec-tools-0.6.5-r2 (02 Jul 2007)

  02 Jul 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +ipsec-tools-0.6.5-r2.ebuild, -files/racoon.init.d.clip, 
  -files/racoon.init.d.clip-single.
  Remove init.d script from ebuild (it is now provided by clip-net)
  as well as config file (which is now unused).
  
  20 Jun 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  ipsec-tools-0.6.5-r1.ebuild, files/racoon.init.d.clip, 
  files/racoon.init.d.clip-single:
  Better crypto algorithms. Make setkey verictl entry depend on
  USE clip-devel, since I find no use for it in a production 
  system.

*ipsec-tools-0.6.5-r1 (30 May 2007)

  30 May 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +ipsec-tools-0.6.5-r1.ebuild, files/racoon.init.d.clip, 
  files/racoon.conf.d.clip, +files/racoon.init.d.clip-single:
  Totally revamped racoon startup : we do not try to inherit caps through
  a script, but give them directly to racoon (which seems actually 
  less dangerous), and import all addresses from /etc/conf.d/net, 
  generating a temporary config file in /var/run.
  
  20 Mar 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  ipsec-tools-0.6.5.ebuild,+files/clip-single:
  clip-single support : do not create SA for RMH. Depend on a virtual
  clip-netbase rather than clip-net.
  
  08 Feb 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  ipsec-tools-0.6.5.ebuild:
  Add CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE.

  30 Jan 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  ipsec-tools-0.6.5.ebuild, files/racoon.init.d.clip:
  Add proper IUSE clip-lsm support, switch init script dependency
  from veriexec to reducecap.
  
  22 Jan 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  ipsec-tools-0.6.5.ebuild, files/racoon.init.d.clip,
  +files/racoon.sh:
  Make verictl-aware racoon install work with gentoo init (which 
  sources /etc/init.d/racoon rather than exec'ing it, which precludes
  attaching any veriexec credentials to that file), using a 'bootstrap'
  script that calls racoon with the proper options, and gets the inheritable
  capset bump.

  19 Jan 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  ipsec-tools-0.6.5.ebuild:
  Add verictl support : CAP_SYS_CHROOT/CAP_NET_ADMIN for racoon
  (permitted for the binary, inheritable from the init script),
  CAP_NET_ADMIN for setkey (useful for debug, I'm still not sure
  this is a good idea on a prod. system - coupled with forced caps
  on /etc/ipsec.conf - though : TODO check it).
  
  06 Dec 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  files/racoon.init.d.clip, ipsec-tools-0.6.5.ebuild:
  Remove setkey part, move it to separate script provided by clip-net.
  Bump DEPENDS accordingly.

  21 Nov 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +files/racoon.conf.clip, +files/racoon.conf.d.clip,
  +files/racoon.init.d.clip, +files/psk.txt.clip,
  ipsec-tools-0.6.5.ebuild:
  Actually set up config files for our racoon. This is only an 
  example, and does not support confvar importing like ipsec.conf,
  which is a pain in the a** to maintain. 
  This sets up a privsep'ed racoon, with the slave running as 
  racoon:racoon, chrooted in /etc/ike/chroot.
  Note that we also still use a pretty trivial pre-shared key....

*ipsec-tools-0.6.5 (19 Sep 2006)

  19 Sep 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  ipsec-tools-0.6.5.ebuild:
  Bump up to current gentoo's ~x86, to be compatible with openssl-0.9.8.
  Same DEPEND trivial change, plus marking x86 for convenience.

*ipsec-tools-0.6.2-r1 (01 Aug 2006)

  01 Aug 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  ipsec-tools-0.6.2-r1.ebuild:
  Initial CLIP import. Fix stupid RDEPEND=${DEPEND} that pulled 
  linux-headers on the target...
